               <t:note>
                  <t:date type="foundation" notBefore="1937" notAfter="1938">1937-1938</t:date>
                  <t:desc type="foundation">Ca. 1930 A.M. (= 1937/38 A.D.) Probably the local community.</t:desc>
                  <t:ab type="history">Dabr.
                     The present church building is new; it was built mainly on the donation of the local people: ʾalaqā Ḥāgos, mamhǝr ʾAmmǝhā Gǝddāy Kǝnfa (who provided for the tin roof). Other people contributed with manpower. The clergy of the church consists of 9 priests, 17 deacons, 1 cantor.
</t:ab>
                  <t:ab type="description">2 Mss. were photographed (some 7 recent left behind, including the new copy of the <t:ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT4755GadlaGN">Vita of Gabra Nāzrāwi</t:ref>): 
                     <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESgna001">GNA-001</t:ref> "The Book of the Funeral Rite"</t:ab>
         
                  <t:ab type="tabot">
